public class ScheduleImpl
extends Object

Author:
Hagen Mahnke, Konrad Reiche Schedule is the representation of one potential solution. A Schedule is valid solution if the HardFitness equals 1.0 . From the point of view of genetic algorithms a Schedule is a chromosome.

addCourse

public void addCourse(CourseElementInstance course,
                      int roomIndex,
                      int timeSlotIndex)
Schedules a course into the current schedule by a specified room and a specified time slot. The course is added to the map in order to get the starting time slot and is added as long as its duration is in the room-time-course slots.

Parameters:
course - the course to be added.
roomIndex - the index of the room.
timeSlotIndex - the index of the time slot.
